-- Spain's Liberbank repays 124 mln euros in state rescue funds
-- 
-- Tue Dec 23, 2014 02:47AM EST
-- None



MADRID, Dec 23 (Reuters) - Spain's Liberbank <LBK.MC> said on Tuesday it had repaid 124 million euros that it received as part of the country's 41.3 billion euro ($51 billion) bailout from Europe in 2012.

Repaying the aid should now allow Liberbank to start paying dividends. The bank was listed and restructured following its bailout.Liberbank's rescue was in the form of bonds that could convert into capital, and which were subscribed by Spain's bank restructuring fund FROB.